{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017oPT5aKyszG1NzxwCeUFtN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25\n     2→\n     3→### 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td — code-review (2026-03-25T01:59:00Z)\n     4→\n     5→- HIGH (fixed): `generateSlug('')` returns `''`, creating malformed TD story keys\n     6→- HIGH (fixed): `backlogAppended` reports items as persisted when `projectRoot` is omitted\n     7→- HIGH (fixed): `wordOverlap` exceeds 1.0 with duplicate words, breaking dedup contract\n     8→- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing test for no-projectRoot path\n     9→- LOW (unfixed): `getExistingTdTitles` reconstructs titles from slugs, losing fidelity\n    10→- LOW (unfixed): `createTdStory` implicitly creates `epic-TD` via spread+override without `ensureEpicTd` call\n    11→- Coverage gap: No test for `appendToBacklogFile` append-to-existing path or error handling\n    12→- Architecture: state.ts at 543 lines exceeds 300-line limit (pre-existing)\n    13→\n    14→### 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td — verification (2026-03-25T02:05:00Z)\n    15→\n    16→- AGENTS.md for src/lib was stale — missing retro-to-sprint.ts entry. Fixed.\n    17→- Disk space critically low (45MB free) — BATS tests failed with \"No space left on device\". Cleared npm cache (2.2GB) to free space.\n    18→- All 10 ACs passed unit-testable verification with direct CLI checks\n    19→- Pre-existing files (state.ts at 543 lines, sprint-yaml.test.ts at 388 lines) exceed 300-line limit but were over before this story\n    20→\n    21→### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — create-story (2026-03-25T02:10:00Z)\n    22→\n    23→- Risk: selector.test.ts at 274 lines — adding ~80 lines of new tests may push past 300-line limit, conflicting with AC 9\n    24→- Observation: Original epic had only 2 ACs; expanded to 9 to cover edge cases. Original ACs were underspecified about Tier D gate constraint.\n    25→- Observation: Implementation is ~3 lines in sort comparator. Test changes are the bulk of work.\n    26→\n    27→### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:20:00Z)\n    28→\n    29→No issues reported. All 11 tasks completed cleanly. 4 lines added to selector.ts, 7 test cases added via it.each. Build, vitest (3664 tests), and BATS (307 tests) all pass.\n    30→\n    31→### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — code-review (2026-03-25T02:27:00Z)\n    32→\n    33→- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md missing TD gate documentation\n    34→- MEDIUM (fixed): Test shorthand variables polluted scope; replaced with typed it.each\n    35→- MEDIUM (fixed): Added case-sensitivity and ready-status test cases (2 new tests, total 3666)\n    36→- LOW (unfixed): selector.ts line 103 comment lacks Decision 6c reference\n    37→- LOW (unfixed): keyToTitle() lowercases \"TD\" to \"Td\" — pre-existing\n    38→- Architecture note: TD gate relies on naming convention (TD- prefix) not structured metadata — accepted tradeoff per Decision 6c\n    39→\n    40→### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — create-story (2026-03-25T02:42:00Z)\n    41→\n    42→- Risk: run.ts at 287 lines — adding Docker pre-check + orphan cleanup (~12 lines) brings it to ~299. Any additional pre-flight gates will breach 300-line limit.\n    43→- Observation: duplicate cleanup functions — `cleanupStaleContainers()` in verify/env.ts and `cleanupContainers()` in infra/container-cleanup.ts overlap for verify containers. Harmless but is tech debt.\n    44→- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts is a dead stub — `cleanupOrphanedContainers()` always returns 0. Real logic lives in infra module.\n    45→\n    46→### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:48:00Z)\n    47→\n    48→- Code quality concern: run.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Future additions require extracting helpers.\n    49→- Observation: run.test.ts at 947 lines, far exceeding 300-line limit. AC#9 says no modified file exceeds 300 lines but test files routinely exceed. Followed existing pattern.\n    50→- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts stub tests fully rewritten — implementation changed from no-op to delegation.\n    51→\n    52→### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — code-review (2026-03-25T02:52:00Z)\n    53→\n    54→- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md files for infra and commands modules were stale\n    55→- LOW (unfixed): `isDockerAvailable()` uses `docker --version` not `docker info` — only checks CLI presence, not daemon. Pre-existing across codebase.\n    56→- LOW (unfixed): Double `isDockerAvailable()` call — run.ts checks, then cleanupContainers() checks again. Harmless overhead.\n    57→- Architecture concern: docker --version vs docker info gap means AC#1 may not catch daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed case. Pre-existing design decision.\n    58→\n    59→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — create-story (2026-03-25T03:05:00Z)\n    60→\n    61→- Risk: docker-setup.ts at 299 lines — adding backend-aware compose selection will push past 300-line limit\n    62→- Risk: formatters.ts at 574 lines (pre-existing violation) — any additions worsen it\n    63→- Risk: state.ts at 293 lines — adding backend field + migration pushes close to 300\n    64→- Observation: Epic says \"ELK\" but code uses OpenSearchBackend (OpenSearch = OSS Elasticsearch fork). User-facing `--observability-backend elk` maps to internal 'opensearch'. Documented in anti-patterns.\n    65→- Observation: Codebase well-prepared — ObservabilityBackend interface, VictoriaBackend, OpenSearchBackend all exist. Main gap is CLI selector and backend-aware health check dispatch.\n    66→\n    67→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — dev-story (2026-03-25T03:15:00Z)\n    68→\n    69→- docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Any future change requires extraction.\n    70→- formatters.ts grew from 574 to 597 lines (pre-existing violation, grew by 23 lines). Backend-aware checks in 3 functions each needed guards.\n    71→- Missing getElkComposeFilePath mock caused silent failure in init-project tests — fixed by adding mock and defensive writeState before Docker setup.\n    72→- ELK compose endpoints not backend-specific — DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS still show Victoria ports even for ELK backend. Known gap, not in ACs.\n    73→\n    74→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — code-review (2026-03-25T03:25:00Z)\n    75→\n    76→- HIGH (fixed): Missing CLI validation for --observability-backend — unsafe `as` cast allows arbitrary strings\n    77→- MEDIUM (fixed): ELK compose file resolution — 4 formatter functions resolved to Victoria compose even for ELK backend\n    78→- MEDIUM (fixed): Wrong endpoints displayed for ELK — Victoria ports shown instead of OpenSearch ports\n    79→- MEDIUM (fixed): resolveEndpoints() not backend-aware — always returned Victoria defaults\n    80→- LOW (unfixed): --no-observability vs --observability-backend none have subtly different semantics\n    81→- LOW (unfixed): formatters.ts at 605 lines — pre-existing violation, now worse\n    82→- LOW (unfixed): docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — fragile\n    83→- Coverage gap: No integration tests for full init --observability-backend elk CLI flow\n    84→- Architecture: buildScopedEndpoints() uses Victoria-specific URL patterns meaningless for ELK\n    85→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"38809bab-d371-4c03-b647-b7b7381ee002","uuid":"d8750fdd-73ac-4448-81b9-d07bd350ae31","timestamp":"2026-03-24T23:27:16.424Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25\n\n### 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td — code-review (2026-03-25T01:59:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): `generateSlug('')` returns `''`, creating malformed TD story keys\n- HIGH (fixed): `backlogAppended` reports items as persisted when `projectRoot` is omitted\n- HIGH (fixed): `wordOverlap` exceeds 1.0 with duplicate words, breaking 