 line 103 comment lacks Decision 6c reference\n- LOW (unfixed): keyToTitle() lowercases \"TD\" to \"Td\" — pre-existing\n- Architecture note: TD gate relies on naming convention (TD- prefix) not structured metadata — accepted tradeoff per Decision 6c\n\n### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — create-story (2026-03-25T02:42:00Z)\n\n- Risk: run.ts at 287 lines — adding Docker pre-check + orphan cleanup (~12 lines) brings it to ~299. Any additional pre-flight gates will breach 300-line limit.\n- Observation: duplicate cleanup functions — `cleanupStaleContainers()` in verify/env.ts and `cleanupContainers()` in infra/container-cleanup.ts overlap for verify containers. Harmless but is tech debt.\n- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts is a dead stub — `cleanupOrphanedContainers()` always returns 0. Real logic lives in infra module.\n\n### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:48:00Z)\n\n- Code quality concern: run.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Future additions require extracting helpers.\n- Observation: run.test.ts at 947 lines, far exceeding 300-line limit. AC#9 says no modified file exceeds 300 lines but test files routinely exceed. Followed existing pattern.\n- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts stub tests fully rewritten — implementation changed from no-op to delegation.\n\n### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — code-review (2026-03-25T02:52:00Z)\n\n- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md files for infra and commands modules were stale\n- LOW (unfixed): `isDockerAvailable()` uses `docker --version` not `docker info` — only checks CLI presence, not daemon. Pre-existing across codebase.\n- LOW (unfixed): Double `isDockerAvailable()` call — run.ts checks, then cleanupContainers() checks again. Harmless overhead.\n- Architecture concern: docker --version vs docker info gap means AC#1 may not catch daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed case. Pre-existing design decision.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — create-story (2026-03-25T03:05:00Z)\n\n- Risk: docker-setup.ts at 299 lines — adding backend-aware compose selection will push past 300-line limit\n- Risk: formatters.ts at 574 lines (pre-existing violation) — any additions worsen it\n- Risk: state.ts at 293 lines — adding backend field + migration pushes close to 300\n- Observation: Epic says \"ELK\" but code uses OpenSearchBackend (OpenSearch = OSS Elasticsearch fork). User-facing `--observability-backend elk` maps to internal 'opensearch'. Documented in anti-patterns.\n- Observation: Codebase well-prepared — ObservabilityBackend interface, VictoriaBackend, OpenSearchBackend all exist. Main gap is CLI selector and backend-aware health check dispatch.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — dev-story (2026-03-25T03:15:00Z)\n\n- docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Any future change requires extraction.\n- formatters.ts grew from 574 to 597 lines (pre-existing violation, grew by 23 lines). Backend-aware checks in 3 functions each needed guards.\n- Missing getElkComposeFilePath mock caused silent failure in init-project tests — fixed by adding mock and defensive writeState before Docker setup.\n- ELK compose endpoints not backend-specific — DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS still show Victoria ports even for ELK backend. Known gap, not in ACs.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — code-review (2026-03-25T03:25:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): Missing CLI validation for --observability-backend — unsafe `as` cast allows arbitrary strings\n- MEDIUM (fixed): ELK compose file resolution — 4 formatter functions resolved to Victoria compose even for ELK backend\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Wrong endpoints displayed for ELK — Victoria ports shown instead of OpenSearch ports\n- MEDIUM (fixed): resolveEndpoints() not backend-aware — always returned Victoria defaults\n- LOW (unfixed): --no-observability vs --observability-backend none have subtly different semantics\n- LOW (unfixed): formatters.ts at 605 lines — pre-existing violation, now worse\n- LOW (unfixed): docker-setup.ts at exactly 300 lines — fragile\n- Coverage gap: No integration tests for full init --observability-backend elk CLI flow\n- Architecture: buildScopedEndpoints() uses Victoria-specific URL patterns meaningless for ELK\n","numLines":85,"startLine":1,"totalLines":85}}}
