{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012RAQEyzPkM7qYAPMEYepYB","type":"tool_result","content":"   465→### Decision 10: Verification Environment — Stack-Aware Provisioning\n   466→\n   467→**Problem:** Docker verify container under-provisioned for every project. Missing Rust version, system libs, clippy, tarpaulin. Fixed manually EVERY verification. PATH not inherited.\n   468→\n   469→**Decision:** Verification Dockerfile is generated per-project based on detected stacks, not selected from a static template.\n   470→\n   471→```typescript\n   472→// src/modules/verify/env.ts\n   473→function generateVerifyDockerfile(stacks: StackDetection[]): string {\n   474→  const sections: string[] = [];\n   475→\n   476→  // Base image\n   477→  sections.push('FROM ubuntu:22.04');\n   478→  sections.push('ENV PATH=\"/root/.cargo/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH\"');\n   479→\n   480→  // Common tools\n   481→  sections.push('RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl jq git python3 pipx');\n   482→  sections.push('RUN pipx install semgrep showboat');\n   483→\n   484→  // Per-stack tooling\n   485→  for (const detection of stacks) {\n   486→    const provider = getStackProvider(detection.stack);\n   487→    sections.push(provider.getVerifyDockerfileSection());\n   488→  }\n   489→\n   490→  // OTLP config\n   491→  sections.push('ENV OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://host.docker.internal:4318');\n   492→\n   493→  return sections.join('\\n\\n');\n   494→}\n   495→```\n   496→\n   497→Each `StackProvider` provides its verify Dockerfile section:\n   498→- **Rust:** Install rustup + stable toolchain + cargo-tarpaulin + clippy + system libs\n   499→- **Node.js:** Install Node.js + npm\n   500→- **Python:** Install pip + coverage\n   501→\n   502→The Dockerfile is generated at `verify-env build` time, not selected from a static file. This ensures it always matches the project's needs.\n   503→\n   504→---\n   505→\n   506→### Decision 11: Process Enforcement — Embedded Quality Gates\n   507→\n   508→**Problem:** Docker pre-check missing (wastes 30-min sessions). Subagents don't update status (reported 7+ times). Time budget ignored (3 sessions failed at verification). Architecture docs too large (>10k tokens).\n   509→\n   510→**Decision:** Five embedded gates in harness-run:\n   511→\n   512→| Gate | Where | What |\n   513→|------|-------|------|\n   514→| **Docker pre-check** | Step 1 pre-flight | `docker info` — fail fast if Docker not running |\n   515→| **Orphan cleanup** | Step 1 pre-flight | Remove leftover `codeharness-verify` containers |\n   516→| **State reconciliation** | Step 1 pre-flight | Rebuild sprint-state.json from sprint-status.yaml |\n   517→| **Time budget check** | Before each phase (3b, 3c, 3d) | Defer if remaining < estimated phase duration |\n   518→| **Status ownership** | After each subagent | Orchestrator owns all status writes — verify and fix |\n   519→\n   520→**Subagent status enforcement:** Remove all instructions that tell subagents to update sprint-status.yaml. Subagents are read-only on state. The orchestrator reads the subagent's output, determines the status transition, and writes it. This is the only reliable pattern.\n   521→\n   522→**Time budget awareness:**\n   523→```\n   524→Phase estimates:\n   525→  create-story: 5 min\n   526→  dev-story: 15 min\n   527→  code-review: 10 min\n   528→  verification: 20 min\n   529→  retro: 5 min\n   530→\n   531→Before each phase: if remaining_time < phase_estimate, defer.\n   532→```\n   533→\n   534→---"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AE5uy3isqvp9ZhM1WQjpz4","session_id":"38809bab-d371-4c03-b647-b7b7381ee002","uuid":"87f19b4a-df09-4909-b0c5-8b22b87d8ef3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T23:33:12.190Z"}
