{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LajJ3fbarEEN5GjSiA5y24","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 14-5: Stack-Aware Verification Dockerfile Generation\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer verifying a Rust/Bevy project,\n     8→I want the verification Dockerfile generated with the correct toolchain and system libs,\n     9→So that verification doesn't waste time fixing container issues manually.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a Rust project with `bevy` in Cargo.toml, when `verify-env build` runs, then the generated Dockerfile includes: correct Rust version, Bevy system libs (wayland, udev, alsa, x11, xkbcommon, fontconfig), clippy, cargo-tarpaulin <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `ENV PATH=\"/root/.cargo/bin:$PATH\"` in the generated Dockerfile, when `cargo tarpaulin` is run inside the container, then it works without manual `source \"$HOME/.cargo/env\"` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 10 (Stack-Aware Provisioning).** Verification Dockerfile is generated per-project based on detected stacks, not selected from a static template.\n    19→\n    20→The `generateVerifyDockerfile()` function (from architecture-v3.md):\n    21→\n    22→```typescript\n    23→// src/modules/verify/env.ts\n    24→function generateVerifyDockerfile(stacks: StackDetection[]): string {\n    25→  const sections: string[] = [];\n    26→\n    27→  // Base image\n    28→  sections.push('FROM ubuntu:22.04');\n    29→  sections.push('ENV PATH=\"/root/.cargo/bin:/usr/local/bin:$PATH\"');\n    30→\n    31→  // Common tools\n    32→  sections.push('RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y curl jq git python3 pipx');\n    33→  sections.push('RUN pipx install semgrep showboat');\n    34→\n    35→  // Per-stack tooling\n    36→  for (const detection of stacks) {\n    37→    const provider = getStackProvider(detection.stack);\n    38→    sections.push(provider.getVerifyDockerfileSection());\n    39→  }\n    40→\n    41→  // OTLP config\n    42→  sections.push('ENV OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT=http://host.docker.internal:4318');\n    43→\n    44→  return sections.join('\\n\\n');\n    45→}\n    46→```\n    47→\n    48→Each `StackProvider` needs a `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` method (add to interface if not present):\n    49→\n    50→**RustProvider:**\n    51→```dockerfile\n    52→# Install Rust toolchain\n    53→RUN curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh -s -- -y --default-toolchain stable\n    54→RUN rustup component add clippy\n    55→RUN cargo install cargo-tarpaulin\n    56→\n    57→# Bevy system libs (if bevy detected)\n    58→RUN apt-get install -y libudev-dev libasound2-dev libwayland-dev libxkbcommon-dev libfontconfig1-dev libx11-dev\n    59→```\n    60→\n    61→**NodejsProvider:**\n    62→```dockerfile\n    63→RUN curl -fsSL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_20.x | bash -\n    64→RUN apt-get install -y nodejs\n    65→```\n    66→\n    67→**PythonProvider:**\n    68→```dockerfile\n    69→RUN apt-get install -y python3-pip python3-venv\n    70→RUN pip3 install coverage pytest\n    71→```\n    72→\n    73→The current `src/modules/verify/env.ts` already exists. Modify it to use the stack provider pattern instead of hardcoded Dockerfile selection. The Bevy detection should check Cargo.toml `[dependencies]` for `bevy` and conditionally include the system libs.\n    74→\n    75→The `PATH` issue is critical: Rust tools installed via rustup are in `/root/.cargo/bin`. Setting `ENV PATH` in the Dockerfile ensures all subsequent `RUN` and runtime commands find cargo, rustc, clippy, and tarpaulin without sourcing `.cargo/env`.\n    76→\n    77→## Files to Change\n    78→\n    79→- `src/modules/verify/env.ts` — Rewrite `generateVerifyDockerfile()` to iterate stack providers and compose Dockerfile sections\n    80→- `src/lib/stacks/types.ts` — Add `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` to `StackProvider` interface (if not already present)\n    81→- `src/lib/stacks/rust.ts` — Implement `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` with Rust toolchain, clippy, tarpaulin, and conditional Bevy system libs\n    82→- `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` — Implement `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` with Node.js install\n    83→- `src/lib/stacks/python.ts` — Implement `getVerifyDockerfileSection()` with Python/pip/coverage install\n    84→- `src/commands/verify-env.ts` — Ensure `build` subcommand calls `generateVerifyDockerfile()` with detected stacks\n    85→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01AE5uy3isqvp9ZhM1WQjpz4","session_id":"38809bab-d371-4c03-b647-b7b7381ee002","uuid":"3c0befad-96cb-4657-a9bb-20910fb7dce6","timestamp":"2026-03-24T23:34:05.861Z"}
