{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F1hjbjF1qmXRhQ1jFf4Ywm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# src/lib/stacks — Stack Provider System\n     2→\n     3→Encapsulates per-language logic behind the `StackProvider` interface. Each provider implements detection, coverage, OTLP instrumentation, Dockerfile generation, and test parsing for one technology stack.\n     4→\n     5→## Files\n     6→\n     7→| File | Purpose | Key Exports |\n     8→|------|---------|-------------|\n     9→| types.ts | Canonical type definitions — `StackProvider` interface, `StackName`, `AppType`, coverage/OTLP/test types | `StackProvider`, `StackName`, `AppType`, `CoverageToolName`, `CoverageToolInfo`, `OtlpResult`, `TestCounts` |\n    10→| registry.ts | Provider registry — registration, lookup, marker-based stack detection | `registerProvider`, `getStackProvider`, `detectStacks`, `detectStack`, `StackDetection`, `_resetRegistry` |\n    11→| nodejs.ts | Node.js provider — app type detection, coverage (c8/vitest/jest), OTLP packages, Dockerfile (node:22-slim), test output parsing | `NodejsProvider` |\n    12→| python.ts | Python provider — app type detection, coverage (pytest-cov), OTLP packages, Dockerfile, test output parsing | `PythonProvider` |\n    13→| rust.ts | Rust provider — Cargo.toml parsing, coverage (tarpaulin), OTLP packages, multi-stage Dockerfile (rust:1.82-slim), workspace test aggregation | `RustProvider` |\n    14→| utils.ts | Shared helpers for providers — safe JSON/text reading, Node.js/Python/Cargo dependency extraction | `readJsonSafe`, `readTextSafe`, `getNodeDeps`, `getPythonDepsContent`, `hasPythonDep`, `getCargoDepsSection`, `hasCargoDep` |\n    15→| index.ts | Barrel re-exports + auto-registers NodejsProvider, PythonProvider, RustProvider on import | all public API from types.ts and registry.ts |\n    16→\n    17→## Architecture\n    18→\n    19→- `StackProvider` interface in `types.ts` defines the contract (15 methods, 1 optional)\n    20→- Each stack gets its own file (`nodejs.ts`, `python.ts`, `rust.ts`)\n    21→- `registry.ts` stores providers in a module-level `Map<StackName, StackProvider>`\n    22→- `index.ts` triggers auto-registration on import\n    23→- `utils.ts` provides shared filesystem helpers used across providers\n    24→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01UEcnB3h2gZqmEJqfPaXmt4","session_id":"38809bab-d371-4c03-b647-b7b7381ee002","uuid":"0c8cd476-de54-4ff9-a903-603c0884e9e8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T23:43:10.228Z"}
